-- Mexico Tourist Arrivals at Airports Rise 13% to December Record
-- B y   N a c h a   C a t t a n
-- 2012-01-26T14:21:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/mexico-tourist-arrivals-at-airports-rise-13-to-december-record.html
Mexico  received 1.07 million foreign
visitors at its airports in December, 13 percent more than a
year earlier and a record for the last month of the year, the
Ministry of Tourism said.  It was the fifth consecutive month of increased visitor
numbers, the ministry, known as Sectur, said in a  statement  on
its website today. U.S. visitors increased by 11 percent from
the previous December, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nacha Cattan in Mexico City at 
 ncattan@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 